'''Miyoshi Shrine''' (三吉神社) is a Shinto shrine located in 8-chome of Minami 1-jo Nishi, Chuo Ward, {{ill|Sapporo|ja|札幌市|12=draft}} in {{ill|Hokkaido|ja|北海道|12=draft}}. Its former shrine rank under the modern shrine ranking system, {{ill|Modern Shrine Ranking System|ja|近代社格制度|lt=Former Shrine Rank|lt_ja=旧社格|12=draft}}, was that of a Prefectural Shrine.

The shrine’s origin dates back to {{ill|1878|ja|1878|12=draft}} (the 11th year of the {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft}} era), when a branch spirit of the {{ill|Taiheizan Miyoshi Shrine|ja|太平山三吉神社|12=draft}} of {{ill|Akita Prefecture|ja|秋田県|12=draft}} was enshrined. In {{ill|1879|ja|1879|12=draft}} (the 12th year of the Meiji era) the shrine was relocated to its present site, and in {{ill|1930|ja|1930|12=draft}} (the 5th year of the {{ill|Showa|ja|昭和|12=draft}} era) it was elevated to Prefectural Shrine status.

Due to its central location within Sapporo, the shrine is well loved by the local citizens, and its annual festival on {{ill|May 15|ja|5月15日|12=draft}} is celebrated in grand scale compared to other shrines in the city.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|12=draft}}}}
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主|lt=Ōkuninushi|lt_ja=大己貴神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Sukunahikona|ja|スクナビコナ|lt=Sukunahikona|lt_ja=少彦名神|12=draft}}
* Fujiwara Miyoshi God
* {{ill|Kotohira Shrine|ja|金刀比羅宮|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Tenmangu Shrine|ja|天満宮|12=draft}}

== External Links ==
* [https://miyoshi-sapporo.or.jp/ Sapporo Miyoshi Shrine]
* [http://www.hokkaidojinjacho.jp/data/01/01002.html Miyoshi Shrine] (Hokkaido Shrine Association website)

