'''Miyoshi Shrine''' (三吉神社) is a Shinto shrine located in 8-chome of Minami 1-jo Nishi, Chuo Ward, {{ill|Sapporo|ja|札幌市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sapporo|qq=}} in {{ill|Hokkaido|ja|北海道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkaido|qq=}}. Its former shrine Rank under the modern shrine Ranking system, {{ill|Modern Shrine Ranking System|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|lt=Former Shrine Rank|lt_ja=旧社格|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern Shrine Ranking System|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=}}, was that of a Prefectural Shrine.

The shrine’s origin dates back to {{ill|1878|ja|1878|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1878|qq=}} (the 11th year of the {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} era), when a branch spirit of the {{ill|Taiheizan Miyoshi Shrine|ja|太平山三吉神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taiheizan Miyoshi Shrine|qq=}} of {{ill|Akita Prefecture|ja|秋田県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita Prefecture|qq=}} was enshrined. In {{ill|1879|ja|1879|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1879|qq=}} (the 12th year of the Meiji era) the shrine was relocated to its present site, and in {{ill|1930|ja|1930|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1930|qq=}} (the 5th year of the {{ill|Showa|ja|昭和|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Showa|qq=}} era) it was elevated to Prefectural Shrine status.

Due to its central location within Sapporo, the shrine is well loved by the local citizens, and its annual festival on {{ill|May 15|ja|5月15日|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 15|qq=}} is celebrated in grand scale compared to other shrines in the city.

