'''Miyoshi Shrine''' (三吉神社) is a Shinto shrine located in 8-chome of Minami 1-jo Nishi, Chuo Ward, {{ill|Sapporo|en|Sapporo|qid=Q37951|lt=Sapporo|1=Sapporo}} in {{ill|Hokkaido|en|Hokkaido|qid=Q35581|lt=Hokkaido|1=Hokkaido}}. Its former shrine Rank under the modern shrine Ranking system, {{ill|Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|en|Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qid=Q712534|lt=Former Shrine Rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}, was that of a Prefectural Shrine.

The shrine’s origin dates back to {{ill|1878|en|1878|qid=Q7776|lt=1878|1=1878}} (the 11th year of the {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} era), when a branch spirit of the {{ill|Taiheizan Miyoshi Shrine|ja|太平山三吉神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taiheizan Miyoshi Shrine|qq=}} of {{ill|Akita Prefecture|en|Akita Prefecture|qid=Q81863|lt=Akita Prefecture|1=Akita Prefecture}} was enshrined. In {{ill|1879|en|1879|qid=Q7783|lt=1879|1=1879}} (the 12th year of the Meiji era) the shrine was relocated to its present site, and in {{ill|1930|en|1930|qid=Q18787|lt=1930|1=1930}} (the 5th year of the {{ill|Shōwa era|en|Shōwa era|qid=Q327567|lt=Showa|1=Shōwa era}} era) it was elevated to Prefectural Shrine status.

Due to its central location within Sapporo, the shrine is well loved by the local citizens, and its annual festival on {{ill|May 15|en|May 15|qid=Q2562|lt=May 15|1=May 15}} is celebrated in grand scale compared to other shrines in the city.

